INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('135', '1', '2013-09-23 02:21:08', '2013-09-23 02:21:08', '<em>“Through the practice of Partner Yoga, the duality of self/other begins to dissolve and we experience directly the essence of Yoga- union.”</em> The Pleasures &amp; Principles of Partner Yoga by Elysabeth Williamson\n\nExperiencing union and dissolving the illusion of separation is the goal and path of partner yoga. The root meaning of yoga is union or joining, in other words to come into <em>union and join</em> with universal divine spirit. Traditionally, the guru or teacher  guides the yoga student along the way, in partner yoga, we become the gurus for each other.\n\nPartner Yoga is an emerging practice with some aspects of Tantra, like Partner Yoga, tantra is a word with many misconceptions. Tantra is not exclusively about sex and for lovers only, the word Tantra essentially means to weave. Partner Yoga also holds the philosophy of using relationship as a tool for awakening to our true nature and connecting to our higher selves.\n\n<img alt=\"partner-yoga5\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/partner-yoga5-300x180.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"180\" /> The practice of Partner Yoga helps bring our relation patterns into balance. In our partner, we have a mirror, a physical presence that brings us deeper into the present moment and more fully into our infinite selves. Just as in our relationships off the mat, in Partner Yoga we experience directly what it feels like to build trust, compassion, and intimacy with others. Our partners reflect back to us the qualities that we express. This is both the pleasure and the challenge of Partner Yoga, because we are made acutely aware of those moments when we are shut down, distrustful, and unwilling to open and connect.\n\n<img alt=\"partner-yoga4\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/partner-yoga4-300x195.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"195\" />Partner Yoga teaches the fundamental value of joining and sharing with others through way of partner and group asana. In addition, Partner Yoga Bliss uses healing art tools such as, mantra, pranayama, and thai massage. I’d like to emphasize that Partner Yoga is not for lovers only – it can be practiced by any two or more willing participants- friends, acquaintances, siblings, parents and children.', 'Partners Yoga ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '94-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 02:21:08', '2013-09-23 02:21:08', '', '94', '/2013/09/23/94-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('136', '1', '2013-09-23 02:21:29', '2013-09-23 02:21:29', '&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Partner Yoga Bliss</h1>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"partner-yoga1\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/partner-yoga1-300x184.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"184\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>“Through the practice of Partner Yoga, the duality of self/other begins to dissolve and we experience directly the essence of Yoga- union.”</em> The Pleasures &amp; Principles of Partner Yoga by Elysabeth Williamson\r\n\r\nExperiencing union and dissolving the illusion of separation is the goal and path of partner yoga. The root meaning of yoga is union or joining, in other words to come into <em>union and join</em> with universal divine spirit. Traditionally, the guru or teacher  guides the yoga student along the way, in partner yoga, we become the gurus for each other.\r\n\r\nPartner Yoga is an emerging practice with some aspects of Tantra, like Partner Yoga, tantra is a word with many misconceptions. Tantra is not exclusively about sex and for lovers only, the word Tantra essentially means to weave. Partner Yoga also holds the philosophy of using relationship as a tool for awakening to our true nature and connecting to our higher selves.\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"partner-yoga5\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/partner-yoga5-300x180.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"180\" /> The practice of Partner Yoga helps bring our relation patterns into balance. In our partner, we have a mirror, a physical presence that brings us deeper into the present moment and more fully into our infinite selves. Just as in our relationships off the mat, in Partner Yoga we experience directly what it feels like to build trust, compassion, and intimacy with others. Our partners reflect back to us the qualities that we express. This is both the pleasure and the challenge of Partner Yoga, because we are made acutely aware of those moments when we are shut down, distrustful, and unwilling to open and connect.\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"partner-yoga4\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/partner-yoga4-300x195.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"195\" />Partner Yoga teaches the fundamental value of joining and sharing with others through way of partner and group asana. In addition, Partner Yoga Bliss uses healing art tools such as, mantra, pranayama, and thai massage. I’d like to emphasize that Partner Yoga is not for lovers only – it can be practiced by any two or more willing participants- friends, acquaintances, siblings, parents and children.', 'Partners Yoga ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '94-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 02:21:29', '2013-09-23 02:21:29', '', '94', '/2013/09/23/94-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
