INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('374', '2', '2016-02-21 11:04:11', '2016-02-21 21:04:11', '<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MWC_RetreatPoster_Web.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-medium\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MWC_RetreatPoster_Web-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>:: UPCOMING YOGA &amp; WELLNESS RETREATS ::   join for 1 to 7 days, your choice! </strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n************************************************************************************************\n\nNO ACCOMODATIONS  ::    you can find many choices in our neighborhood though!\n\nR\n\n************************************************************************************************\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Aerial-Circus-March-Retreat.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-508\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Aerial-Circus-March-Retreat-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Aerial Circus March Retreat\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>March 18th-24th Aerial Circus Bootcamp in Maui!</strong>\n\nFacebook:  https://www.facebook.com/events/204627219887977/#\nA Phoenix Circus Production, Co-facilitated by the Elvolutionaries, Marley and Freyja Skye.\n<a href=\"http://www.elvolutionaries.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.elvolutionaries.com</a>\n\nRetreat Costs:::: (Book before Feb 15th for 10% Discount)\n\nNo Catering\n$120 —full day of classes\n$60 half day\n$750 - Full 7 Day Retreat\n\nWith Catering: local, organic, gourmet from professional catering to your needs<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">\n(Veg, Vegan, Raw, etc)\n$170 - full day of classes\n$110 half day\n$1100 - Full 7 Day Retreat</span>\n\nAerial Circus Bootcamp Maui will introduce beginner students to aerial silks, while supporting the learning with proper stretching and conditioning techniques. Morning runs, yoga, acroyoga and acrobatics classes will help create the foundational core work that aerial silks requires. Intermediate aerial students will be taught more advanced techniques.\nAerial Silks shares the benefits of traditional yoga such as flexibility, strength and balance while being suspended in the air. Transform yoga into dance! Flying dance! Teachings will focus on climbing techniques, foot locks, hip locks, stalls, drops, and introductory aerial silks poses. Aerial swing techniques will also be covered to assist with inversions and backbends.\nMarley Skye from Phoenix Circus, Canada has taught aerial silks and other circus arts to students of all ages for the past eight years. Classes are challenging, fun and made accessible for all levels of physical fitness.\nExperience Yoga in the air! Yoga is excellent conditioning for preparing for aerial silks. The added gravity and height of aerial silks assists students in increasing their strength and flexibility at a rapid rate. Students will start with low flying techniques, and gradually progress higher.\nStretch and mobilize with a friend! Marley Skye will also be teaching beginner acro yoga classes. Acroyoga is fun, promotes flexibility and employs Thai Massage and gravity to allow deep stretching of muscles, tendons, and bones.\n\nTypical daily schedule\n• 08:00 - 09:00 Group Run, Stretch &amp; Meditation\n• 09:00 - 11:00 Aerial Silks with Marley Skye\n• 11:00 - 12:00 Fresh and local organic brunch\n• 12:00 - 16:00 Free time to explore, get a massage, read through the yoga and spirituality books in the library, relax in the hammocks, swim in waterfalls, etc.\n• 16:00 - 18:00 Acro Yoga &amp; Aerial Silks with Marley Skye\n• 18:00 - 19:00 Delicious delightful dinner of local and organic goodness\n• 19:00 - 21:00 Magical evening activities (different every night)\n\nInstructor\n__________________________<wbr />______________\nMarley Skye\n\nMarley has been studying yoga and athletics since he was a teenager in 1996, and trained in wrestling and track &amp; field under two Olympic level coaches. This early intense training, combined with his passion for arts music and dance propelled him through a unique and self-explorative journey to physical mastery and artistic expression. Marley teaches that each person has a unique path to growth, empowerment and creative expression that needs to be balanced between dreams, personal discipline, play, transformation, creativity and external teaching.\n\nThe next chapter of Marley’s life was filled with travel and schooling. Marley graduated from University of British Columbia with a bachelors in Asian Languages. A Mandarin major, and a Sanskrit, Tibetan and Hindi Minor led him to deepen his personal practice by combining Chinese acupressure massage techniques and Sanskrit mantras to help awaken and empower the energy body and nerve channels.\n\nIn 2007, Marley Skye met dancer and circus aerial acrobat, Freyja and co-founded the Elvolutionaries, an aerial circus performance troupe. Together, they trained and performed aerial circus storytelling shows. Combining circus, theatre, and music the troupe travelled the west coast of North America, and began producing shows for festivals, private and corporate events.\nWanting to share this inspiration and empower people with what he had learned, Marley began directing circus classes and retreats in 2009. In that time, Skye has facilitated community classes at recreation centers, Pirate Circus Bootcamps (sailing &amp; circus retreat), Indoor &amp; Outdoor Aerial Circus Retreats, as well as currently running weekly classes for kids and adults.\n\nSince then, Marley has performed and directed aerial and dance shows at local and international events, including Envision, Symbiosis, Burning Man, Shambala, Diversity Festival, Komasket, Big Time Out, Mystic Island Festival, BassCoast, and numerous other events, as well as community fundraisers, government events, and private events all over the West Coast of British Columbia in the last 8 years.\n\nIn the past three years, he became the director of Phoenix Circus, as well as the creator and director of “Sweet &amp; Salty Burlesque”, a neo-burlesque permaculture circus &amp; dance troupe.\nAn avid learner and multi-talented performer, Marley Skye is inspired by collaboration, innovation and the ability to constantly re-invent ourselves. Marley also teaches firespinning, stiltwalking, juggling, hand balancing, aerial pole, aerial hoop, and costume making, and is a vast resource for learning the circus arts.\nMarley Skye brings the passion and devotion of an multi-talented independent artist focused on inspiring others with circus arts to fly through the skies towards their dreams.\n\nFreyja’s Skye\n\nOriginally from Germany, Freyja Skye moved to Montreal in 2004 to pursue studies in Contemporary dance. Journeying to the west coast in the summer introduced her to the festival culture and the rich circus arts scene, which inspired her to learn aerial arts – first silks, then Lyra, pole and most recently Spanish Web. After a couple of years in the dance program at Concordia University and another year at Main Dance in Vancouver, she literally ran away with the circus and joined MythMaker on tour for a season. This inspired her to get her own, veggie-oil powered circus bus, and upon meeting Marley Skye in 2007, ‘The Elvolutionaries’ circus troupe was born, travelling across BC and beyond to perform and teach aerial acrobatics and dance at countless music festivals, private and corporate events until the present day.\nAs a performer, Freyja embodies wild power and sensual grace.\n‘It is important to remember what our role is as performers. We are here to inspire, to reflect back what we receive from the audience, to show them that it is possible to pursue our wildest dreams and reach our full potential!’\n\nA passionate contact dancer, Freyja has also been teaching contact improvisation for years, now blending it with acrobatics, acro yoga and circus.\nFreyja’s biggest inspiration in teaching is: ‘I love to make people fly! It is so empowering to defy gravity, push beyond what we thought our limits were, and it is so rewarding for me to see my students get upside down, feel weightless, and discover their own power!’', 'RETREATS', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '352-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-02-21 11:04:11', '2016-02-21 21:04:11', '', '352', 'http://mauitropicalmassage.com/352-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
