INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('460', '2', '2015-09-14 07:31:42', '2015-09-14 17:31:42', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AdrianThailand.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-363\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AdrianThailand-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Maui Yoga &amp; Wellness Retreat instructor\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<b>Adrians bio:</b>   <b>Adrian </b>has been studying massage &amp; yoga passionately since 2004.  He chose one of the best massage schools in the world,  Maui School of Therapuetic Massage, graduating in September 2010 where he honed his skills in <b>Lomi Lomi, Swedish, Sports Massage, NMT, Deep Tissue</b>, and more.  Upon request he can also introduce sound therapy with Tibetan Healing bowls, and a high end <b>Tactile</b> <b>Sound Healing</b> table.  He spent 9 months in India studying at various yoga schools, ashrams &amp; meditations centers including a 2 month yoga intensive at <a title=\"Agama Yoga School \" href=\"http://www.AgamaYoga.com\" target=\"_blank\">Agama Yoga</a> in Rishikesh, India followed by a 500 hours/3 month teachers training at their mother school in Koh Phangan, Thailand.  He prefers to teach meditation at the moment but can do private yoga classes upon request.\r\n\r\n<em>He continues his education constantly learning to help people lighten up &amp; ENLIGHTEN UP with Yoga, Massage, Meditation &amp; Sound Healing.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Experience</em> ::  *650 hour/ 12 month Massage Therapy program - September 2010 in Maui, Hawaii.\r\n\r\n*500 hours/3month Hatha Yoga teachers training at Agama Yoga in Koh Phangan, Thailand in 2009.\r\n\r\n*5 extra months of yoga intensive trainings at Agama Yoga school in Rishikesh, India Sept/Oct 2007 &amp; Thailand 2009.\r\n\r\n<b>*</b>Yoga University – June &amp; August 2013, Maui-Hawaii\r\n\r\n<b>*</b>Access Bars – energy healing training July 2013, Maui-Hawaii.\r\n\r\n*Kailash School of Ayurveda Massage – October 2006.  3 week course in Dharamsala, India.\r\n\r\n*Sunshine School of Thai Massage – June 2009, 10 day course in Chang Mai, Thailand.\r\n\r\n*Lomi Lomi 2 day intensive workshop – July 2005, Vancouver BC.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Tirzah-bio-headshot.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-362\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Tirzah-bio-headshot-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Maui Yoga teacher &amp; Massage LMT\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong>Tirzah\'s bio:  </strong>Tirzah is a cheerful, certified yoga instructor, professional massage therapist, sacred sexuality advocate and hula hoop enthusiast. She has been happily practicing yoga for over a decade. She deeply resonates with the Tantric path as it has captivated her with its extraordinary teachings for many years. Tirzah has studied extensively for five months at Agama Tantra Yoga University in Thailand. She is wholeheartedly passionate about spiritual evolution, as it continues to shift her consciousness in profound ways. <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">                          </span>Tirzah is a citizen of the world and has received the richest education through travel. She genuinely adores culture shock, barefeet, dreaming, acro yoga flying, coconuts, laughter, writing, celebrations, expansion, waterslides and being upside down. And she LOVES love. Tirzah is highly optimistic about living fully and focuses her time and energy on experiences rather than material things. She is currently working on quieting her crazy ego, following her heart\'s footsteps, and recognizing challenges as grand opportunities for growth.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Neenel\'s bio:  </strong>Neenel is a body centered life coach who is dedicated to personal growth and transformation. She holds a Bachelors degree in Community Studies from the University of California, Santa Cruz.   She is a 400hr certified yoga teacher who received her foundational training at Kailash Tribal Yoga School in Dharmasala, India and continued her training in the US, studying Kundalini Yoga, as taught by Yogi Bhajan.  Currently, she is working towards her Counseling Masters degree.  Her professional background also includes working locally in community mental health, co-facilitating clinical counseling groups, and leading forty day transformational retreats.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-35 aligncenter\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Lola6-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"Lola6\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Lola’s bio:</strong>  Lola  has an extensive and diversified background in yoga, movement, and music. Her esoteric, yoga and dance studies range in subject matter from Hatha Yoga, Naam Yoga, Pilates, Belly Dance, Jazz Dance, Gyrotonic, West African, Harmonyum, astro-physics with the Resonance Project, Merkabah Meditation, Theta Healing, music production and Classical as well as Jazz Vocal Studies.\r\n\r\nIn addition, she likes to explore ancient and modern healing techniques while inquiring within her own heart and higher spirit for guidance to a more sustainable and healthier way of living, such as permaculture, Theta healing meditation, essential oils for natural health and living in community. Most recently, she\'s dancing for Iona 360 Dance Company  Maui chapter  (contemporary, experimental dance ), she\'s excited to start dancing professionally again.\r\n\r\nWhen she’s not at her studio teaching, taking a workshop, singing or making music, Lola enjoys chanting to the ocean waves, hiking to waterfalls, being outside amongst the trees, exploring raw super-food recipes, and sun gazing.\r\n\r\n<b> </b><em>experience ::</em>\r\n\r\n<b>*</b>Yoga University – June &amp; August 2013, Maui-Hawaii\r\n\r\n<b>*</b>Access Bars – energy healing training July 2013, Maui-Hawaii.\r\n\r\n*Yoga Works- 200 hour Hatha Yoga 2011, Mill Valley, CA.\r\n\r\n* Naam Yoga– 200 hour yoga specializing in mantra, meditation, kundalini, kabalah, numerology and mudras. Santa Monica, CA\r\n\r\n*Harmonyum- energy work accessing sunlight energy to clear karma. Santa Monica, CA\r\n\r\n*Acro Yoga- Wanderlust Festival, 2010, 2011, 2012\r\n\r\n*Pilates- Integrative Teacher Training, Im=X Pilates, Joseph Pilates Method and Advanced Exercises, Many workshops on post-rehabilitative exercises\r\n\r\n*Gyrotonic and Gyrokinesis Certified Miami Beach including Jump Board Certification\r\n\r\n*Living Light Raw Foods Educator Certification 2010, Mendocino, CA\r\n\r\n*Zumba Certification 2010, Santa Cruz, CA\r\n\r\n*Theta Healing Plant, Animal and Soul Mate Workshop 2013, Idaho Falls, ID\r\n\r\n* Essential Oils workshops at DoTerra University\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b> </b>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 07:31:42', '2015-09-14 17:31:42', '', '5', 'http://mauitropicalmassage.com/5-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
