INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('516', '2', '2016-02-21 11:04:58', '2016-02-21 21:04:58', '<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MWC_RetreatPoster_Web.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-medium\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MWC_RetreatPoster_Web-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>:: UPCOMING YOGA &amp; WELLNESS RETREATS ::   join for 1 to 7 days, your choice! </strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nNO ACCOMODATIONS  ::    you can find many choices in our neighborhood though!\r\n\r\nRETREAT BY DONATION ::  yeah, its our way of saying Mahalo!\r\n\r\n************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Aerial-Circus-March-Retreat.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-508\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Aerial-Circus-March-Retreat-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Aerial Circus March Retreat\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>March 18th-24th Aerial Circus Bootcamp in Maui!</strong>\r\n\r\nFacebook:  https://www.facebook.com/events/204627219887977/#\r\nA Phoenix Circus Production, Co-facilitated by the Elvolutionaries, Marley and Freyja Skye.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.elvolutionaries.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.elvolutionaries.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAerial Circus Bootcamp Maui will introduce beginner students to aerial silks, while supporting the learning with proper stretching and conditioning techniques. Morning runs, yoga, acroyoga and acrobatics classes will help create the foundational core work that aerial silks requires. Intermediate aerial students will be taught more advanced techniques.\r\nAerial Silks shares the benefits of traditional yoga such as flexibility, strength and balance while being suspended in the air. Transform yoga into dance! Flying dance! Teachings will focus on climbing techniques, foot locks, hip locks, stalls, drops, and introductory aerial silks poses. Aerial swing techniques will also be covered to assist with inversions and backbends.\r\nMarley Skye from Phoenix Circus, Canada has taught aerial silks and other circus arts to students of all ages for the past eight years. Classes are challenging, fun and made accessible for all levels of physical fitness.\r\nExperience Yoga in the air! Yoga is excellent conditioning for preparing for aerial silks. The added gravity and height of aerial silks assists students in increasing their strength and flexibility at a rapid rate. Students will start with low flying techniques, and gradually progress higher.\r\nStretch and mobilize with a friend! Marley Skye will also be teaching beginner acro yoga classes. Acroyoga is fun, promotes flexibility and employs Thai Massage and gravity to allow deep stretching of muscles, tendons, and bones.\r\n\r\nTypical daily schedule\r\n• 08:00 - 09:00 Group Run, Stretch &amp; Meditation\r\n• 09:00 - 11:00 Aerial Silks with Marley Skye\r\n• 11:00 - 12:00 Fresh and local organic brunch\r\n• 12:00 - 16:00 Free time to explore, get a massage, read through the yoga and spirituality books in the library, relax in the hammocks, swim in waterfalls, etc.\r\n• 16:00 - 18:00 Acro Yoga &amp; Aerial Silks with Marley Skye\r\n• 18:00 - 19:00 Delicious delightful dinner of local and organic goodness\r\n• 19:00 - 21:00 Magical evening activities (different every night)\r\n\r\nInstructor\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\nMarley Skye\r\n\r\nMarley has been studying yoga and athletics since he was a teenager in 1996, and trained in wrestling and track &amp; field under two Olympic level coaches. This early intense training, combined with his passion for arts music and dance propelled him through a unique and self-explorative journey to physical mastery and artistic expression. Marley teaches that each person has a unique path to growth, empowerment and creative expression that needs to be balanced between dreams, personal discipline, play, transformation, creativity and external teaching.\r\n\r\nThe next chapter of Marley’s life was filled with travel and schooling. Marley graduated from University of British Columbia with a bachelors in Asian Languages. A Mandarin major, and a Sanskrit, Tibetan and Hindi Minor led him to deepen his personal practice by combining Chinese acupressure massage techniques and Sanskrit mantras to help awaken and empower the energy body and nerve channels.\r\n\r\nIn 2007, Marley Skye met dancer and circus aerial acrobat, Freyja and co-founded the Elvolutionaries, an aerial circus performance troupe. Together, they trained and performed aerial circus storytelling shows. Combining circus, theatre, and music the troupe travelled the west coast of North America, and began producing shows for festivals, private and corporate events.\r\nWanting to share this inspiration and empower people with what he had learned, Marley began directing circus classes and retreats in 2009. In that time, Skye has facilitated community classes at recreation centers, Pirate Circus Bootcamps (sailing &amp; circus retreat), Indoor &amp; Outdoor Aerial Circus Retreats, as well as currently running weekly classes for kids and adults.\r\n\r\nSince then, Marley has performed and directed aerial and dance shows at local and international events, including Envision, Symbiosis, Burning Man, Shambala, Diversity Festival, Komasket, Big Time Out, Mystic Island Festival, BassCoast, and numerous other events, as well as community fundraisers, government events, and private events all over the West Coast of British Columbia in the last 8 years.\r\n\r\nIn the past three years, he became the director of Phoenix Circus, as well as the creator and director of “Sweet &amp; Salty Burlesque”, a neo-burlesque permaculture circus &amp; dance troupe.\r\nAn avid learner and multi-talented performer, Marley Skye is inspired by collaboration, innovation and the ability to constantly re-invent ourselves. Marley also teaches firespinning, stiltwalking, juggling, hand balancing, aerial pole, aerial hoop, and costume making, and is a vast resource for learning the circus arts.\r\nMarley Skye brings the passion and devotion of an multi-talented independent artist focused on inspiring others with circus arts to fly through the skies towards their dreams.\r\n\r\nFreyja’s Skye\r\n\r\nOriginally from Germany, Freyja Skye moved to Montreal in 2004 to pursue studies in Contemporary dance. Journeying to the west coast in the summer introduced her to the festival culture and the rich circus arts scene, which inspired her to learn aerial arts – first silks, then Lyra, pole and most recently Spanish Web. After a couple of years in the dance program at Concordia University and another year at Main Dance in Vancouver, she literally ran away with the circus and joined MythMaker on tour for a season. This inspired her to get her own, veggie-oil powered circus bus, and upon meeting Marley Skye in 2007, ‘The Elvolutionaries’ circus troupe was born, travelling across BC and beyond to perform and teach aerial acrobatics and dance at countless music festivals, private and corporate events until the present day.\r\nAs a performer, Freyja embodies wild power and sensual grace.\r\n‘It is important to remember what our role is as performers. We are here to inspire, to reflect back what we receive from the audience, to show them that it is possible to pursue our wildest dreams and reach our full potential!’\r\n\r\nA passionate contact dancer, Freyja has also been teaching contact improvisation for years, now blending it with acrobatics, acro yoga and circus.\r\nFreyja’s biggest inspiration in teaching is: ‘I love to make people fly! It is so empowering to defy gravity, push beyond what we thought our limits were, and it is so rewarding for me to see my students get upside down, feel weightless, and discover their own power!’', 'RETREATS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '352-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-21 11:04:58', '2016-02-21 21:04:58', '', '352', 'http://mauitropicalmassage.com/352-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('509', '2', '2016-01-27 22:03:18', '2016-01-28 08:03:18', '<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MWC_RetreatPoster_Web.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-medium\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MWC_RetreatPoster_Web-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>:: UPCOMING YOGA &amp; WELLNESS RETREATS ::   join for 1 to 7 days, your choice! </strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n**********************************************************************************\r\n\r\n*Note...there are 2 upcoming retreats.  1) Feb 4-10th &amp; 2) March 18-24th.  Scroll below to see the later one.\r\n\r\n***********************************************************************************\r\n\r\n<strong>February 4th-10th  </strong>Aerial Yoga Play retreat feat. Jen Healy &amp; Lucid Dawn teaching many other styles of Yoga &amp; Wellness!  Plus live music/dance evenings &amp; more!    See more info on her website:  <a href=\"http://www.AerialYogaPlay.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.AerialYogaPlay.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/BioPic1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-483\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/BioPic1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"BioPic1\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>February:</strong> 4th-10th, 2016\r\n\r\n~~AERIAL YOGA PLAY RETREAT &amp; TRAINING IN HAWAII~~\r\n\r\nFebruary 4-10th @ Maui Wellness Center we are pleased to have Bay Area\'s Jen Healy leading Aerial Yoga Play as the featured teacher with special guest yoga teacher LUCID DAWN ( <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lucidyoga.com%2F&amp;h=TAQFIARtW&amp;enc=AZNPQpH1cDEG6phh7SMLiV70uJ0lXlEdYOm3ZQa8z93Nl7iTQLhNvNIgPN-hldCaOIw&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.lucidyoga.com.</a> ) Live music provided by Ronnie/Eenor. <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eenor.com%2F&amp;h=1AQHhptYX&amp;enc=AZOsqvf29_MJESKzXJvz3UQrVqUtO4gjdxSbX7pbsxfq1bgfAZ86aNEZqXDnCkf5yio&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.eenor.com</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.AerialYogaPlay.com%2F&amp;h=nAQGU54zp&amp;enc=AZP8b93NWoDrOjxmP-szrZwfUVVnoTHex1bRciA8mraRztfpBfq21AhNXAsrnXKPH3s&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.AerialYogaPlay.com</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/jenhealy1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.youtube.com/user/<wbr />jenhealy1</a>\r\n\r\nIn this week long retreat, we give you several options to accommodate you travel schedule as well as time to enjoy the natural beauty of Hawaii...\r\n*Choose to come for 1 day, 3 days, 5 days, all 7 days!?!\r\nYou can come for the retreat and/ OR the training OR just have fun in one of the workshops :))\r\n\r\n<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">\r\n3 OPTIONS:\r\n-- RETREAT ONLY: $175/day (up to 7 days)\r\n-- JUST THE WORKSHOPS: $50/day drop-in (4-6pm)\r\n-- TEACHER TRAINING: $600-1200 (Basic --&gt; Advanced)</span>\r\n\r\n*Accommodations are not included from these prices.\r\n\r\nDetails below....\r\n\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n\r\nWhat’s included ::\r\n\r\nCamping only (off site accommodations otherwise)\r\nDaily organic brunch and dinner\r\nMorning Hatha, Kundalini or Vinyasa practice\r\nMorning meditation and pranayama sessions\r\nAfternoon Aerial Yoga Play workshops\r\nSound Healing sessions &amp; Ecstatic Dance\r\nEvening festivities\r\n\r\nWhat’s not included ::\r\n*Extra activities during free time are not included in the price.\r\n*Sleeping accommodations\r\n\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n\r\n** ONLY 8 SPACES AVAILABLE SO RESERVE NOW.\r\nPre-register at <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.aerialyogaplay.com%2F&amp;h=MAQHcaJCH&amp;enc=AZP44haTL8uGbJM2cdgj2hY-_jgrW5RU7Kn9UJMkOPl5rP-kVtnwy3sFq-SuEkExM2o&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.aerialyogaplay.com</a> as there are very limited spaces for yoga swings in our studio.\r\n\r\nEmail for more info: jen@zenhealyng.com\r\n\r\nGood Times Yoga &amp; Aerial Yoga Play (AYP) classes, workshops &amp; daily meditations, + many optional activities (massage, waterfall swims, hikes, kayak &amp; snorkel adventures, surf lessons, etc...). Come treat yourself to a relaxing experience!\r\n\r\nJoin us for just the Aerial Yoga Play, just the yoga/retreat component, or the entire event!\r\n\r\nMORE INFO here ::\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zenhealyng.com%2Fevent%2Faerial-yoga-play-hawaii-retreat-training%2F&amp;h=dAQGfPAJ2&amp;enc=AZMLVgM2fmjMg9HR7WmBry0mBoAjpEyMhEL2dKuEu_Fz-mHH7AAUKst2J6aCzyU_ILM&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">http://www.zenhealyng.com/<wbr />event/<wbr />aerial-yoga-play-hawaii-ret<wbr />reat-training/</a>\r\n\r\nRSVP HERE:: ONLY 8 SPACES LEFT\r\n<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zenhealyng.com%2Fstore-2%2Fproducts%2Fteacher-trainings%2F&amp;h=xAQF29V0j&amp;enc=AZOFP3tKiCCXwNDTuFXiSrv6fGqnWi3k696GLIC3aavkd8Y_6oP7QuvISDVGfnaC3aA&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">http://www.zenhealyng.com/<wbr />store-2/products/<wbr />teacher-trainings/</a>\r\n\r\n***************\r\n\"A spiritual retreat is a means of touching in with the core of our beings for a period of time. The process of leaving daily routines behind and interrupting the habitual thoughts that occupy our minds moves us from being fixed to being open.\"\r\n(Liah Howard)\r\n\r\n**************\r\nTEACHER TRAINING SCHEDULE::\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n**Morning free or partake in the retreat activities\r\n12-4pm AYP Certification Program\r\n*4-6pm Aerial Yoga Play Workshop (open to everyone)\r\n*Drop-ins $50 [INCLUDED IN THE TRAINING &amp; RETREAT]\r\n6-7pm Delicious delightful dinner of local and organic goodness\r\n7-9pm Sound healing, party yoga, Magic movie nights, ecstatic dance night, fire circle potluck, etc.\r\n\r\nPRICES :: $600-1200 for AYP TRAINING PROGRAM\r\n\r\nBasic Certification (2 days): $600\r\nIntermediate Certification (4 days): $900\r\nAdvanced Certification (6 days): $1200\r\n\r\nSIGN UP BY JANUARY 4, 2016 FOR THE 10% DISCOUNT\r\nUSE COUPON CODE: ZENGIFT20\r\n\r\nRSVP HERE:: ONLY 8 SPACES LEFT\r\n<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zenhealyng.com%2Fstore-2%2Fproducts%2Fteacher-trainings%2F&amp;h=DAQH5FO2g&amp;enc=AZMj0MbIH3iemlTdCfP-Ufg4S3SAHVhmigmJLOygatP6K-P5JIoYxnokzOF67gWBSKE&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">http://www.zenhealyng.com/<wbr />store-2/products/<wbr />teacher-trainings/</a>\r\n\r\nRETREAT SCHEDULE::\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n8-9am: Meditation &amp; Pranayama\r\n9-11: LUCID YOGA (special guest teacher)\r\n11-12: Super fresh organic brunch\r\n12-4: Free time to explore, get a massage, read through our amazing 30+ yoga/spirituality library &amp; relax in the hammocks, swim in waterfalls...\r\n\r\n4-6: AYP WORKSHOP (Jen Healy)\r\n\r\n6-7: Delicious Delightful Dinner of local, organic goodness!\r\nOptional: 7-9pm: Magical evening activities (different each night)\r\n\r\nEvening Events :: 7-9pm\r\n*Thursday night: Opening circle and talent show\r\n*Friday night: Good Times Yoga w/ Nona Fender\r\n* Saturday night: Ecstatic Dance w/ DJ Boogiemeister\r\n*Sunday night: open for adventure\r\n* Monday night: Mystic Movie Night\r\n*Tuesday evening: evening sound journey with Mystic Alchemy (crystal bowls)\r\n*Wednesday night: 11-11 Closing celebration circle with Jen Healy &amp; Lucid Dawn\r\n\r\nExtra Options: Massage &amp; Sound Healing Table, Hikes including picnic at waterfalls nearby &amp; Twin Falls adventure, Hula Hoop &amp; poi classes, fire circle potlucks, Kayaking tours, Surf lessons, Zipline, Spa day at Temple of Peace for chlorine free hot tub/sauna &amp; steam room.\r\n\r\n**Come for the RETREAT ONLY @ $175 per day.\r\nChoose the # of days you would like to join us.\r\n\r\n**Come for the afternoon workshop only-- $50 drop-in\r\n\r\nSIGN UP BY JANUARY 4, 2016 FOR THE 10% DISCOUNT\r\nUSE COUPON CODE: ZENGIFT10\r\n\r\nRSVP HERE:: ONLY 8 SPACES LEFT\r\n<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zenhealyng.com%2Fstore-2%2Fproducts%2Fteacher-trainings%2F&amp;h=8AQG8BJqy&amp;enc=AZMIvujvgYm-eJ5OtMVRjekz7PYDbf3djWnKiV_i1jiGbpeU2wwpNEEdb3ZAXqLmxaQ&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">http://www.zenhealyng.com/<wbr />store-2/products/<wbr />teacher-trainings/</a>\r\n\r\nAccomodations not included in the pricing. OPTIONS::\r\n1. Camping (limited)\r\n2. Heather\'s Cabin\'s ($50-75 per night or $300-350 for the week)\r\n3. Hale Akua- Lori Grace\'s EcoCenter close by (mid-range prices)\r\n<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fhaleakuagardenfarm.com%2F&amp;h=FAQEA9Yxu&amp;enc=AZPR_csi9edv0NO483ojUCubIaNoQ46wny3LTYUSFIBreoM35TuB8F3Qp9dtkJZJUTg&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">http://<wbr />haleakuagardenfarm.com/</a>\r\n4. AIRB&amp;B (amazing places nearby) or Lumeria Reatreat Center (higher end pricing). Check online for availability.\r\n\r\nOVERVIEW\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n\r\n9-11am Daily YOGA Schedule;\r\nspecialized live music yoga work/ play shops each day;\r\n\r\n1. Deep Intention Setting - Embody your truth. Create golden bridges of your samskaras. We will use the Lifeline Technique in conjunction with the physical and meditative practices of Yoga to communicate with the subconscious mind and program in changes that last.\r\n\r\n2. Ritual Yoga - using traditional earth based indigenous practices combined w/ yoga to deeply honor the elements of our body/ mind and environment. To maintain balance in life and instill personal practices that extend off of the mat and into life.\r\n\r\n3. Nada Yoga - dive in to the yoga of sound and vibration. co-led by Eenor, find your bodys natural resonance. Use vocalizations to find more strength and space. Be washed in transcendental sound from our multi-instrumentalist musician magician while led into the sacred depths of your bodymind in the physical and meditative practices of yoga.\r\n\r\n4. Yin &amp; Restorative Yoga - a slow, supported, receptive practice to integrate the learning and transformation initiated on retreat. Allow the fascial system to melt away any old habitual holds and renew the bodymind.\r\n\r\n5. Therapeutic Yoga - we will address any injuries or issues that retreat guests have and also talk about other common injuries and issues and how to relieve or prevent them. Great for teachers.\r\n\r\n6. Yoga Playtime - partner yoga, some acro yoga, and theatre games. Discover new aspects of yourself, how to practice with others and ways to discover your unique voice and offering in the world.\r\n\r\n&amp; Friday night, 7-9pm, \"Good Times Yoga\" w/ Nona Fender &amp; the Benders. Bring your superhero selves on an adventure in yoga playland! A combination interactive yoga class-act, social dance party, comedy show, and theater class set to live booty shaking music. Just a little naughty and a whole lot of fun. Celebrate the sacred profane!\r\n\r\nWhat’s included ::\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n\r\nDaily organic brunch and dinner\r\nMorning Hatha, Kundalini or Vinyasa practice\r\nMorning meditation and pranayama sessions\r\nEvening Aerial Yoga Play class\r\nSound Healing sessions &amp; Ecstatic Dance\r\nEvening festivities\r\n__________________________<wbr />________________\r\n\r\nAerial Yoga Play explained ::\r\n\r\nLet your yoga take flight and swing your way into feeling fit while having fun! Aerial Yoga Play allows a combination of benefits similar to aerial yoga, pilates, suspended resistance training, acrobatics, and dance all rolled into one for an amazing suspended fitness experience. It allows for all the benefits of traditional yoga- flexibility, strength and balance – with the unique conditioning of aerial dance and acrobatics for an exhilarating new way of approaching yoga. Sculpt your body in the air, using our special yoga swings, as you tone muscles, find balance, and increase flexibility.\r\n\r\nJen Healy’s Aerial Yoga Swings are specially made to be supportive, stretchy, and comfortable. They support your body in your yoga practice and increase your ability to enter into challenging poses, like backbends and inversions, with more safety and ease.\r\n\r\nCome discover how the Aerial Yoga Play swings are one of the most effective tools you can use to suspend the body, open up the spine, and create more space in the neck and lower back which provides a unique advantage in rehabilitating these commonly strained areas.\r\n\r\nAerial Yoga Play is creating one of the most beneficial ways of using gravity to accelerate healing, while building strength, balance, and openness.\r\n\r\n__________________________<wbr />________\r\n\r\nOptional Activities during your free time ::\r\n\r\n• Hikes and picnic at waterfalls nearby and Twin Falls adventure\r\n• Hula hoop and poi classes\r\n• Kayaking tours with Andrea\r\n• Massage and sound healing table\r\n• Spa at Temple of Peace for chlorine-free hot tub/sauna and steam room\r\n• Surf lessons with Mattius\r\n• Fire circle potlucks\r\n• Life Coaching/Quantum Healyng by Jen Healy\r\n• Zip line\r\n\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n\r\nWhat’s included ::\r\n\r\nCamping only (off site accommodations otherwise)\r\nDaily organic brunch and dinner\r\nMorning Hatha, Kundalini or Vinyasa practice\r\nMorning meditation and pranayama sessions\r\nAfternoon Aerial Yoga Play workshops\r\nYoga and naturopathy workshop and lectures\r\n\r\nWhat’s not included ::\r\n*Extra activities during free time are not included in the price.\r\n*Sleeping accommodations\r\n\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\n\r\n**Come for the Retreat only-- Average of $175 per day.\r\nChoose the # of days you would like to join us.\r\n\r\n**Come for the afternoon workshop only-- $50 drop-in\r\n\r\nSIGN UP BY JANUARY 4, 2016 FOR THE 10% DISCOUNT\r\nUSE COUPON CODE: ZENGIFT10\r\n\r\nRSVP HERE:: ONLY 8 SPACES LEFT\r\n<a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zenhealyng.com%2Fstore-2%2Fproducts%2Fteacher-trainings%2F&amp;h=3AQH0sZrv&amp;enc=AZNo6JDq6CsyIJPxYOMhtfJuZbPInkGENO9VLpC1jEt2i0AVv-IuYDMhVObUPwPkQtM&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">http://www.zenhealyng.com/<wbr />store-2/products/<wbr />teacher-trainings/</a>\r\n\r\nINSTRUCTORS\r\n__________________________<wbr />_________\r\n\r\nJEN HEALY :: M.S. , CMT , Master Practitioner\r\n\r\nJen Healy is a leader in \"Quantum Energetics.\" She has focused her mastery on bridging the gap between science, spirituality, and the healing arts. She combines her Master\'s in Electrical Engineering and Physics with numerous wisdom tools from Eastern and Western philosophies to offer a unique style of Being Engineering and Energy Management.\r\n\r\nAs the founder and CEO of Zen Healyng and Healyng Technologies, she offers over 15 years of experience bringing together the best information and excellence in Quantum Healyng Technologies, Energetics/Energy Management, Advanced Body Therapy, Conscious Movement, Empowerment and Evolutionary practices.\r\n\r\nShe is dedicated to advancing the healing arts through a blending of spirituality, somatics, nutrition, yoga therapy, dance, movement, and meditation with the sciences. Her love for sacred geometry and quantum physics inform and inspire her work. As a pioneer and revolutionary, she embodies this new wave of Conscious Movement to awaken the body, mind, and soul. The Quantum Playground and Aerial Yoga Play are some of here recent creations for empowering embodiment practices.\r\n\r\nHer courses seemlessly weave together all of her knowledge and experience to offer a truly Integrative, Informative, and Deeply Transformative Experience. She believes that the true Self in inherently magnificent and powerful beyond measure; therefore, a good daily practice will support a person\'s natural empowerment process.\r\n\r\nShe is currently coaching her Empowerment Program at Universities to top scholars who are women in science and engineering. She finds this opportunity to offer empowerment tools to students entering into the fields of science deeply rewarding.\r\n\r\nLUCID DAWN BIO:\r\nLucid Dawn is a synthesist. Her greatest superpower is to transform pain, fear &amp; sickness, into wisdom, strength &amp; freedom, and to help others to find their superpowers!\r\nLucid has been on the Yogic path since 1994, five years into recovery from an abject early life of illness and abuse. On this journey she has learned many healing modalities. She does not subscribe to one \'style\', but honors and integrates many. She is thriving as a mother, wife, teacher, community organizer, ritual leader &amp; artist.\r\nLucid is fervent in her desire to help others thrive. She weaves the teachings of Yoga; movement, breath, meditation, &amp; Non-Dual Tantrik philosophy w/ ritual &amp; practice that acknowledge; season, celestial movements, and phases of life. Lucid also spent many years in theater and circus. She includes the use of sound healing &amp; expressive arts in the yoga practice. Her studies in healing cancer and chronic illness, neuroscience, cellular biology, nutrition, essential oils, Non-Violent Communication, earth magick, energy medicine, &amp; Lifeline Healing Technique also inform her teaching.\r\nShe is dedicated to embracing all beings &amp; all aspects of being for a full celebration of life, including courageously facing death .\r\nPrimary Yoga &amp; Healing TRAINING;\r\nRYT 500+\r\n200+hrs @Yoga Tree SF,2007 primary teacher, Janet Stone\r\nAnusara training 200+ hrs w/ Sianna Sherman, Abby Tucker, Desree Rumbaugh\r\nYoga for Cancer &amp; Chronic Illness w/ Jnani Chapman\r\nNon Dual Tantrik Saivism w/ Hareesh Wallis &amp; Mattamayura Institute\r\nCertified Practitioner of the Lifeline Healing Technique w/Dr. Darren Weissman\r\n\r\nEENOR BIO:\r\nEenor is a many dimensional multi-instrumentalist, songwriter, producer, and performer who has been received enthusiastically by audiences all over Europe and America. he\'s enjoyed many musical adventures from touring Europe with Plainfield (an infamous S.F.punk band) , to studying with Indian Sarod master Ali Akbar Khan, to rocking the nation with Les Claypool’s Frog Brigade. You’ve heard his guitar on the soundtrack of comedy central’s Southpark for years. Eenor also recently toured worldwide for many years with The Yard Dog Road Show... an innovative cabaret cartoon ride through America’s past and future.\r\n\r\nEenor is currently introducing a few new projects.\r\n\r\nhis new rocktronic act Mus Mezmer is a multi-styled sonic blend of electronic and live performance arts. It is a solo show combining technology, mixed media, and good ole fashioned songwriting, think Robert Johnson meets Amon Tobin for strong coffee at a remote beach in Maui on a full moon... The first release (May 2013) is available now on soundcloudand bandcamp.\r\n\r\nMus Mezmer is a live electronic show where modern electro styles are merged with old fashioned songwriting and instrumentation. Eenor references many music styles including rock, blues, west african, funk, persian, indian, dubstep, electro, downtempo, drum n bass, punk, sound healing and experimentation, and even classical forms to form sonically surreal and bumpin dream rides. Mus Mezmer successfully debuted recently at the Symbiosis Festival 2012 at Pyramid Lake in Nevada.\r\n\r\nwildeboar electric trio is eenor’s new power trio with Hassan Hurd on drums and Sam Gulisano on bass. They take the classic trio format further with rollercoaster swing and sway, their sound is monstrous and on the verge, their grit is fierce and their gold is butter smooth. A new release is currently being recorded at priairie sun studios for summer 2015 release.\r\n\r\na recent collaboration with the infamous Yoga instructor, Nona Fender has yielded Good Times Yoga with Nona Fender and The Benders, a humorous and wild yoga class that features eenor and other musicians providing the live soundtrack to Nona’s unforgettable blend of the sacred and profane.\r\n\r\neenor has also often been seen onstage sitting in with Beats Antique at various events including Jazzfest 2012 in New Orleans, and also contributed on Yaili Tambur (turkish banjo) to their first 2 CD releases...\r\n\r\nEenor is building electric guitars and other stringed instruments, check them out at <a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2FMezmerGuitars.com%2F&amp;h=8AQG8BJqy&amp;enc=AZPLVPvGnUi7j09skIlK_OdT9AsLQYrzaRibpai9ldQisjHDZe16f5Qz0g-oGnV7mvg&amp;s=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">MezmerGuitars.com</a>\r\n\r\nSend eenor@eenor.net an email and keep in touch for releases.\r\n\r\n************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Aerial-Circus-March-Retreat.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-508\" src=\"http://mauitropicalmassage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Aerial-Circus-March-Retreat-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Aerial Circus March Retreat\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>March 18th-24th Aerial Circus Bootcamp in Maui!</strong>\r\n\r\nFacebook:  https://www.facebook.com/events/204627219887977/#\r\nA Phoenix Circus Production, Co-facilitated by the Elvolutionaries, Marley and Freyja Skye.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.elvolutionaries.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">www.elvolutionaries.com</a>\r\n\r\nRetreat Costs:::: (Book before Feb 15th for 10% Discount)\r\n\r\nNo Catering\r\n$120 —full day of classes\r\n$60 half day\r\n$750 - Full 7 Day Retreat\r\n\r\nWith Catering: local, organic, gourmet from professional catering to your needs<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">\r\n(Veg, Vegan, Raw, etc)\r\n$170 - full day of classes\r\n$110 half day\r\n$1100 - Full 7 Day Retreat\r\n\r\nAerial Circus Bootcamp Maui will introduce beginner students to aerial silks, while supporting the learning with proper stretching and conditioning techniques. Morning runs, yoga, acroyoga and acrobatics classes will help create the foundational core work that aerial silks requires. Intermediate aerial students will be taught more advanced techniques.\r\nAerial Silks shares the benefits of traditional yoga such as flexibility, strength and balance while being suspended in the air. Transform yoga into dance! Flying dance! Teachings will focus on climbing techniques, foot locks, hip locks, stalls, drops, and introductory aerial silks poses. Aerial swing techniques will also be covered to assist with inversions and backbends.\r\nMarley Skye from Phoenix Circus, Canada has taught aerial silks and other circus arts to students of all ages for the past eight years. Classes are challenging, fun and made accessible for all levels of physical fitness.\r\nExperience Yoga in the air! Yoga is excellent conditioning for preparing for aerial silks. The added gravity and height of aerial silks assists students in increasing their strength and flexibility at a rapid rate. Students will start with low flying techniques, and gradually progress higher.\r\nStretch and mobilize with a friend! Marley Skye will also be teaching beginner acro yoga classes. Acroyoga is fun, promotes flexibility and employs Thai Massage and gravity to allow deep stretching of muscles, tendons, and bones.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTypical daily schedule\r\n• 08:00 - 09:00 Group Run, Stretch &amp; Meditation\r\n• 09:00 - 11:00 Aerial Silks with Marley Skye\r\n• 11:00 - 12:00 Fresh and local organic brunch\r\n• 12:00 - 16:00 Free time to explore, get a massage, read through the yoga and spirituality books in the library, relax in the hammocks, swim in waterfalls, etc.\r\n• 16:00 - 18:00 Acro Yoga &amp; Aerial Silks with Marley Skye\r\n• 18:00 - 19:00 Delicious delightful dinner of local and organic goodness\r\n• 19:00 - 21:00 Magical evening activities (different every night)\r\n\r\n\r\nInstructor\r\n__________________________<wbr />______________\r\nMarley Skye\r\n\r\nMarley has been studying yoga and athletics since he was a teenager in 1996, and trained in wrestling and track &amp; field under two Olympic level coaches. This early intense training, combined with his passion for arts music and dance propelled him through a unique and self-explorative journey to physical mastery and artistic expression. Marley teaches that each person has a unique path to growth, empowerment and creative expression that needs to be balanced between dreams, personal discipline, play, transformation, creativity and external teaching.\r\n\r\nThe next chapter of Marley’s life was filled with travel and schooling. Marley graduated from University of British Columbia with a bachelors in Asian Languages. A Mandarin major, and a Sanskrit, Tibetan and Hindi Minor led him to deepen his personal practice by combining Chinese acupressure massage techniques and Sanskrit mantras to help awaken and empower the energy body and nerve channels.\r\n\r\nIn 2007, Marley Skye met dancer and circus aerial acrobat, Freyja and co-founded the Elvolutionaries, an aerial circus performance troupe. Together, they trained and performed aerial circus storytelling shows. Combining circus, theatre, and music the troupe travelled the west coast of North America, and began producing shows for festivals, private and corporate events.\r\nWanting to share this inspiration and empower people with what he had learned, Marley began directing circus classes and retreats in 2009. In that time, Skye has facilitated community classes at recreation centers, Pirate Circus Bootcamps (sailing &amp; circus retreat), Indoor &amp; Outdoor Aerial Circus Retreats, as well as currently running weekly classes for kids and adults.\r\n\r\nSince then, Marley has performed and directed aerial and dance shows at local and international events, including Envision, Symbiosis, Burning Man, Shambala, Diversity Festival, Komasket, Big Time Out, Mystic Island Festival, BassCoast, and numerous other events, as well as community fundraisers, government events, and private events all over the West Coast of British Columbia in the last 8 years.\r\n\r\nIn the past three years, he became the director of Phoenix Circus, as well as the creator and director of “Sweet &amp; Salty Burlesque”, a neo-burlesque permaculture circus &amp; dance troupe.\r\nAn avid learner and multi-talented performer, Marley Skye is inspired by collaboration, innovation and the ability to constantly re-invent ourselves. Marley also teaches firespinning, stiltwalking, juggling, hand balancing, aerial pole, aerial hoop, and costume making, and is a vast resource for learning the circus arts.\r\nMarley Skye brings the passion and devotion of an multi-talented independent artist focused on inspiring others with circus arts to fly through the skies towards their dreams.\r\n\r\nFreyja’s Skye\r\n\r\nOriginally from Germany, Freyja Skye moved to Montreal in 2004 to pursue studies in Contemporary dance. Journeying to the west coast in the summer introduced her to the festival culture and the rich circus arts scene, which inspired her to learn aerial arts – first silks, then Lyra, pole and most recently Spanish Web. After a couple of years in the dance program at Concordia University and another year at Main Dance in Vancouver, she literally ran away with the circus and joined MythMaker on tour for a season. This inspired her to get her own, veggie-oil powered circus bus, and upon meeting Marley Skye in 2007, ‘The Elvolutionaries’ circus troupe was born, travelling across BC and beyond to perform and teach aerial acrobatics and dance at countless music festivals, private and corporate events until the present day.\r\nAs a performer, Freyja embodies wild power and sensual grace.\r\n‘It is important to remember what our role is as performers. We are here to inspire, to reflect back what we receive from the audience, to show them that it is possible to pursue our wildest dreams and reach our full potential!’\r\n\r\nA passionate contact dancer, Freyja has also been teaching contact improvisation for years, now blending it with acrobatics, acro yoga and circus.\r\nFreyja’s biggest inspiration in teaching is: ‘I love to make people fly! It is so empowering to defy gravity, push beyond what we thought our limits were, and it is so rewarding for me to see my students get upside down, feel weightless, and discover their own power!’</span>', 'RETREATS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '352-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-27 22:03:18', '2016-01-28 08:03:18', '', '352', 'http://mauitropicalmassage.com/352-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
